EVAR practice and outcomes - elective EVAR

Number, gender, age, year and stent-graft used

Martin Hennessy

01/10/2019

1 Details about elective EVAR performed

1.1 Timescale covered and number of elective EVAR

  • This document covers elective EVAR performed between 1996-09-19 and 2019-09-24 for abdominal aortic aneurysms
  • ie. common iliac artery aneurysms are excluded as well as symptomatic AAAs, ruptures etc.
  • This comprises 805 elective EVAR
  • Of these, the numbers are split among the Health Boards as detailed below:

1.2 Gender

1.2.1 Number of elective EVAR by gender

  • 10.7% of elective EVAR have been performed in women

1.2.2 Number of elective EVAR performed by gender at each site

  • In GG & C, 11.1% of elective EVAR have been performed in women
  • In FV, 4.3% of elective EVAR have been performed in women

1.3 Age

  • Boxplots are used in this section
  • Here is a reminder of what a boxplot displays:
    • The box represents the interquartile range (IQR) of the data
    • In other words, 50% of the patients fall between this age range
    • The thick black horizontal line is the median age
    • The thin black vertical lines extend to the upper and lower limits of age
    • Black dots represent outliers (above or below 3 x IQR)

1.3.11 Number of elective EVAR by patients decade of life

  • Due to the small number of patients, those who were in their 6th or 10th decades at time of elective EVAR are ommitted from the following.
  • Boxplot of spread of ages in 7th, 8th or 9th decade:

All sites, all years

  • Patients in their 7th decade skew slightly towards the upper aspect of that decade
  • Patients in their 8th decade, the decade in which most elective EVARs are performed, are evenly spread

  • Patients in their 9th decade skew greatly towards the young ages of that decade

  • The median and means from the above boxplot are shown in this table:

Decade Median Mean
7th 66 66.0
8th 75 74.6
9th 82 82.5
